<div class="ads-page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="container mt-4">

                <div class="jumbotron">
                    <h1 class="display-4">Modum Ads API Documentation</h1>
                    <p class="lead">Integrate Modum Ads seamlessly into your website.</p>
                </div>

                <section id="embedding" class="mb-4">
                    <h2>Embedding Ads</h2>
                    <p>
                        To embed Modum Ads on your website, use the following HTML code and replace 'YOUR_API_ENDPOINT'
                        with the actual API endpoint provided by Modum.
                    </p>
                    <pre>
                    <code class="html">
                &lt;div id="modumAdsContainer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

                &lt;script&gt;
                    fetch('YOUR_API_ENDPOINT')
                        .then(response =&gt; response.text())
                        .then(htmlString =&gt; {
                            const container = document.getElementById('modumAdsContainer');
                            if (container) {
                                container.innerHTML = htmlString;
                            }
                        })
                        .catch(error =&gt; console.error('Error fetching ad HTML:', error));
                &lt;/script&gt;
                </code>
            </pre>
                </section>

                <section id="endpoints" class="mb-4">
                    <h2>API Endpoints</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Modum Ads API provides the following endpoints:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <code>/api/ads/mostAddedToFav</code> - Get information about the most added to favorites products.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <code>/api/ads/mostBought</code> - Get information about the most bought products.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section id="examples" class="mb-4">
                    <h2>Examples</h2>
                    <p>
                        Here are examples of how to use the Modum Ads API buttons:
